Description: Fragment of flattened handle from a probably Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, micaceous pink-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and prow symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Pasikrates. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 88, 1
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0233)
